Usage:
        The  `create-config'  program creates a new directory.  It copies and
        processes the sources  from the `src' directory.  By typing `make' or
        `make result'  in this new directory the sources are compiled and the
        sizes and  compilation times of  the resulting objects  are measured.
        The size and time results of the measurements are placed in the files
        `result-size.csv' and `result-time.csv'.
        
        Note,  that additional sources can be downloaded to perform execution
        time measurement.

        To configure the measurement the switches of  `create-config'  can be
        used (type `create-config -h' for the available switches).

